communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Prosperity games
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Detailed documents outlining Information Operations (IO) exercises undertaken between the years of 1992 and 1999. Some of these exercises may include the terms “prosperity games” and should include any detailed findings from these exercises. Please also include any planning and briefing material, which may also include recorded audio video, briefings, powerpoint slideshows, text documents or handwritten notes.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emily Crose

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Evident Surprise - US Navy
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records associated with the 1996/1997 "evident surprise" exercise conducted by US Atlantic Command, later presented to DoD leadership.
Please see the attached news article for additional background information.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Emily Crose
